<item>
            <title>[LU-8268] Interop 2.8&lt;-&gt;2.9 sanity-sec test_16: add_nodemap_range=c1 10.9.6.42@tcp Invalid argument</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8268</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for sarah_lw &amp;lt;wei3.liu@intel.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/f6fbbc88-2d62-11e6-80b9-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/f6fbbc88-2d62-11e6-80b9-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The sub-test test_16 failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;adding fops nodemaps failed 1
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;test log&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;nodemap.add_nodemap_idmap=c0 gid 60004:60002
CMD: trevis-47vm3 /usr/sbin/lctl get_param nodemap.c0.idmap
CMD: trevis-47vm4 /usr/sbin/lctl get_param nodemap.c0.idmap
CMD: trevis-47vm6 /usr/sbin/lctl list_nids | grep tcp | cut -f 1 -d &apos;@&apos;
CMD: trevis-47vm3 /usr/sbin/lctl nodemap_add c1
CMD: trevis-47vm3 /usr/sbin/lctl nodemap_add_range --name c1 --range 10.9.6.42@tcp
CMD: trevis-47vm3 /usr/sbin/lctl list_nids | grep tcp | cut -f 1 -d &apos;@&apos;
CMD: trevis-47vm3 /usr/sbin/lctl list_nids | grep tcp | cut -f 1 -d &apos;@&apos;
CMD: trevis-47vm4 /usr/sbin/lctl list_nids | grep tcp | cut -f 1 -d &apos;@&apos;
CMD: 10.9.6.40 /usr/sbin/lctl set_param nodemap.add_nodemap=c1
nodemap.add_nodemap=c1
CMD: trevis-47vm3 /usr/sbin/lctl list_nids | grep tcp | cut -f 1 -d &apos;@&apos;
CMD: trevis-47vm3 /usr/sbin/lctl list_nids | grep tcp | cut -f 1 -d &apos;@&apos;
CMD: trevis-47vm4 /usr/sbin/lctl list_nids | grep tcp | cut -f 1 -d &apos;@&apos;
CMD: 10.9.6.40 /usr/sbin/lctl set_param nodemap.add_nodemap_range=&apos;c1 10.9.6.42@tcp&apos;
10.9.6.40: error: set_param: setting /proc/fs/lustre/nodemap/add_nodemap_range=c1 10.9.6.42@tcp: Invalid argument
 sanity-sec test_16: @@@@@@ FAIL: adding fops nodemaps failed 1 
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
